line_1: DEAR thoughtless CLARA to my verse attend,
line_2: Believe for once thy lover and thy friend;

line_1: Believe for once thy lover and thy friend;

line_1: Heaven to each sex has various gifts assign'd,
line_2: And shewn an equal care of human-kind;

line_1: And shewn an equal care of human-kind;
line_2: Heaven to each sex has various gifts assign'd,

line_1: Strength does to man's imperial race belong,
line_2: To yours that beauty which subdues the strong;

line_1: To yours that beauty which subdues the strong;
line_2: Strength does to man's imperial race belong,

line_1: But as our strength when misapply'd, is lost,
line_2: And what should save, urges our ruin most;

line_1: And what should save, urges our ruin most;
line_2: But as our strength when misapply'd, is lost,

line_1: Just so, when beauty prostituted lies,
line_2: Of bawds the prey, of rakes th' abandon'd prize,

line_1: Of bawds the prey, of rakes th' abandon'd prize,

line_1: Women no more their empire can maintain,
line_2: Nor hope, vile slaves of lust, by love to reign.

line_1: Nor hope, vile slaves of lust, by love to reign.

line_1: Superior charms but make their case the worse,

line_1: Oh nymph! that might, reclin'd on Cupid's breast,

line_1: Of love, ill-treated and abus'd, that he
